---
<section class="stories" id="stories" aria-labelledby="stories-heading">
  <div class="container">

    <div class="stories-list">

      <!-- Ryan Dressler -->
      <article class="story-entry">
        <img
          class="story-photo"
          src="/images/ryan-dressler.webp"
          alt="Ryan Dressler in Ohio"
          width="160"
          height="160"
          loading="lazy"
        />
        <div class="story-text">
          <h3 class="story-name">Ryan Dressler</h3>
          <p class="story-body">
            Ryan Dressler runs the numbers for a living. He converted fifty acres in Ohio,
            and six years later the fireflies returned, along with the Baltimore orioles and
            a pair of trumpeter swans. As he puts it: the first half of his life was spent
            lobbying for impact investing, and he would like to spend the second half
            lobbying for nature.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- Sara Weaner Cooper -->
      <article class="story-entry">
        <img
          class="story-photo"
          src="/images/sara-weaner-cooper.webp"
          alt="Sara Weaner Cooper's front yard meadow in Pennsylvania"
          width="160"
          height="90"
          loading="lazy"
        />
        <div class="story-text">
          <h3 class="story-name">Sara Weaner Cooper</h3>
          <p class="story-body">
            Sara converted the front lawn of her first house in Pennsylvania. She spent two
            years working with the existing turf rather than tearing it out, and put a small
            sign in the yard so the neighbors would know what was coming. One morning in May,
            the first partridge pea pushed through the grass.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- Victor DeMasi -->
      <article class="story-entry">
        <div
          class="story-photo"
          role="img"
          aria-label="[REPLACE: portrait photograph of Victor DeMasi]"
          data-replace="true"
        ></div>
        <div class="story-text">
          <h3 class="story-name">Victor DeMasi</h3>
          <p class="story-body">
            Victor DeMasi has counted the butterflies in his Connecticut meadow every Fourth
            of July for twenty-eight years. In the mid-nineties he counted five hundred. Last
            year he counted two hundred and fifty.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- David Kaye -->
      <article class="story-entry">
        <img
          class="story-photo"
          src="/images/david-kaye.webp"
          alt="David Kaye at Nod Hill meadow, Connecticut"
          width="160"
          height="120"
          loading="lazy"
        />
        <div class="story-text">
          <h3 class="story-name">David Kaye</h3>
          <p class="story-body">
            David Kaye did not build his meadow to make a point. The strip of land beside
            the brewery was going to become an eyesore, so Nod Hill turned it into the view
            from the beer garden and the filter for the river beside it.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- Doug Tallamy -->
      <article class="story-entry">
        <img
          class="story-photo"
          src="/images/doug-tallamy.webp"
          alt="Doug Tallamy, University of Delaware"
          width="160"
          height="106"
          loading="lazy"
        />
        <div class="story-text">
          <h3 class="story-name">Doug Tallamy</h3>
          <p class="story-body">
            Doug Tallamy watched a bulldozer bury the pond he grew up next to when he was
            in the third grade. He has spent the rest of his life explaining what is lost
            when the ordinary living things disappear &mdash; and how quickly they return when
            the land is given back to them.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>

    </div><!-- /.stories-list -->

    <p class="stories-closing">
      These are the people the film is built around. If your own land
      has a version of this story,{' '}
      <a
        href="mailto:meadowfilm.hello@gmail.com"
        class="stories-link"
      >we would be glad to hear it</a>.
    </p>

  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .stories {
    padding: var(--space-24) 0;
  }

  .stories-lead {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.35;
    max-width: 52ch;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-16);
  }

  .stories-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-12);
  }

  .story-entry {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 80px 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-8);
    align-items: start;
  }

  .story-photo {
    width: 80px;
    height: 80px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    background: linear-gradient(155deg, #2e5028 0%, #4A6741 100%);
    flex-shrink: 0;
    object-fit: cover;
    display: block;
  }

  .story-name {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text);
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .story-body {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.75;
    max-width: 65ch;
  }

  .stories-closing {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-top: var(--space-16);
    max-width: 65ch;
  }

  .stories-link {
    color: var(--color-meadow);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
    transition: opacity var(--duration-fast);
  }

  .stories-link:hover,
  .stories-link:focus-visible {
    opacity: 0.75;
  }

  .stories-link:focus-visible {
    outline: 2px solid var(--color-meadow);
    outline-offset: 3px;
    border-radius: 1px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 520px) {
    .story-entry {
      grid-template-columns: 64px 1fr;
      gap: var(--space-4);
    }

    .story-photo {
      width: 64px;
      height: 64px;
    }
  }
</style>
